Algorithm I would use is:

 1. Find the index of an element matching a condition
 2. Remove and save the object at found index
 3. Insert object at correct index at beginning of array

I should note that if there are duplicates that the order may get mixed up at the front of the array as duplicates are getting inserted at either index 0 or 1;

&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-js --&gt;

